1. record and play sounds
- experimented with different audio formats
- record audio => sounddevice (record audio data as numpy array) & scipy.io.wavfile.write() (to save that numpy array in .wav)
- convert & save audio => .wav to mp3 or vice-versa => pydub (pydub.AudioSegment.from_wav("file.wav")) & export it (.export("file.mp3", format="mp3")) [requires ffmpeg]
- play mp3 => pygame
- play wav => simpleaudio

2. convert speech to text
- using whisper

3. get llm response
- using groq api

4. convert response(text) to speech
- using gTTS

5. play that response
- play mp3 => pygame
